occurrenceRemarks: Seaside Alumroot (Heuchera pilosissima) in the Saxifrage family. Native, perennial plant growing on moist, shaded rocky wall near the coast. Smaller plant than H. micrantha. Flowers are in dense clusters, have less exerted stamens, and are rounder and densely hairy. Calyx lobes are pink-red. Peak bloom time: May-June. Monterey County Wildflowers: a Field Guide, Yeager and Mitchell, 2016, p. 274. Plants of Monterey County: an Illustrated Field Key, 2nd edition, Matthews and Mitchell, 2015, pp. 294-295.
